<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Four specimens (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 48" captionStartId="F48" captionText="Figure 48. Psychronaetes sp. CCZ _ 101. Specimen CCZ _ 063 A in situ image. Specimen CCZ _ 101 B in situ image F dorsal ossicles. Specimen CCZ _ 103 C in situ image H dorsal ossicles. Specimen CCZ _ 104 D in situ image E dorsal view of specimen before preservation G ventral view. Scale bars: 5 cm (A, D); 2 cm (B); 1 cm (E, G); 75 μm (F); 100 μm (H). Image attribution: Durden and Smith (A-D); Wiklund, Durden, Drennan, and McQuaid (E, G); Bribiesca-Contreras (F, H)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.82172.figure48" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716374" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">48A-D</figureCitation>
). Body dorso-ventrally flattened (L = 15.9 cm, W = 3.4 cm), tapering at both ends; pronounced 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“neck”">&quot;neck&quot;</normalizedToken>
anteriorly; mouth anteroventral, anus posterodorsal. Tentacles 18, with long stems and large elongate oval discs (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 48" captionStartId="F48" captionText="Figure 48. Psychronaetes sp. CCZ _ 101. Specimen CCZ _ 063 A in situ image. Specimen CCZ _ 101 B in situ image F dorsal ossicles. Specimen CCZ _ 103 C in situ image H dorsal ossicles. Specimen CCZ _ 104 D in situ image E dorsal view of specimen before preservation G ventral view. Scale bars: 5 cm (A, D); 2 cm (B); 1 cm (E, G); 75 μm (F); 100 μm (H). Image attribution: Durden and Smith (A-D); Wiklund, Durden, Drennan, and McQuaid (E, G); Bribiesca-Contreras (F, H)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.82172.figure48" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716374" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">48G</figureCitation>
). Body wall firm and leathery, dark violet in preserved specimen, with evident, numerous calcareous wheel-like ossicles that make the skin sparkle under light. Mid-ventral ambulacrum is naked; one irregular row of ≥ 40 tube feet running along each ventrolateral ambulacra (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 48" captionStartId="F48" captionText="Figure 48. Psychronaetes sp. CCZ _ 101. Specimen CCZ _ 063 A in situ image. Specimen CCZ _ 101 B in situ image F dorsal ossicles. Specimen CCZ _ 103 C in situ image H dorsal ossicles. Specimen CCZ _ 104 D in situ image E dorsal view of specimen before preservation G ventral view. Scale bars: 5 cm (A, D); 2 cm (B); 1 cm (E, G); 75 μm (F); 100 μm (H). Image attribution: Durden and Smith (A-D); Wiklund, Durden, Drennan, and McQuaid (E, G); Bribiesca-Contreras (F, H)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.82172.figure48" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716374" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">48G</figureCitation>
), very conspicuous on live specimens (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 48" captionStartId="F48" captionText="Figure 48. Psychronaetes sp. CCZ _ 101. Specimen CCZ _ 063 A in situ image. Specimen CCZ _ 101 B in situ image F dorsal ossicles. Specimen CCZ _ 103 C in situ image H dorsal ossicles. Specimen CCZ _ 104 D in situ image E dorsal view of specimen before preservation G ventral view. Scale bars: 5 cm (A, D); 2 cm (B); 1 cm (E, G); 75 μm (F); 100 μm (H). Image attribution: Durden and Smith (A-D); Wiklund, Durden, Drennan, and McQuaid (E, G); Bribiesca-Contreras (F, H)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.82172.figure48" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716374" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">48A-D</figureCitation>
), but fully retracted on preserved specimens. Paired dorsal ambulacra with ~ 20 papillae each; ~ 7 long thick papillae distributed along each ambulacrum, interspersed with smaller ones (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 48" captionStartId="F48" captionText="Figure 48. Psychronaetes sp. CCZ _ 101. Specimen CCZ _ 063 A in situ image. Specimen CCZ _ 101 B in situ image F dorsal ossicles. Specimen CCZ _ 103 C in situ image H dorsal ossicles. Specimen CCZ _ 104 D in situ image E dorsal view of specimen before preservation G ventral view. Scale bars: 5 cm (A, D); 2 cm (B); 1 cm (E, G); 75 μm (F); 100 μm (H). Image attribution: Durden and Smith (A-D); Wiklund, Durden, Drennan, and McQuaid (E, G); Bribiesca-Contreras (F, H)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.82172.figure48" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716374" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">48A-E</figureCitation>
). There are ~ 18 large conical papillae surrounding the anterior margin dorsally, fully fused forming a fringe (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 48" captionStartId="F48" captionText="Figure 48. Psychronaetes sp. CCZ _ 101. Specimen CCZ _ 063 A in situ image. Specimen CCZ _ 101 B in situ image F dorsal ossicles. Specimen CCZ _ 103 C in situ image H dorsal ossicles. Specimen CCZ _ 104 D in situ image E dorsal view of specimen before preservation G ventral view. Scale bars: 5 cm (A, D); 2 cm (B); 1 cm (E, G); 75 μm (F); 100 μm (H). Image attribution: Durden and Smith (A-D); Wiklund, Durden, Drennan, and McQuaid (E, G); Bribiesca-Contreras (F, H)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.82172.figure48" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716374" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">48B, D</figureCitation>
). Dorsal ossicles numerous, wheel-like, of different sizes (ranging from 77-340 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
in diameter) but mostly large; strongly concave; central primary cross with 4-6 struts, mostly four; smooth rim; with 10-16, mostly 12, short spokes (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 48" captionStartId="F48" captionText="Figure 48. Psychronaetes sp. CCZ _ 101. Specimen CCZ _ 063 A in situ image. Specimen CCZ _ 101 B in situ image F dorsal ossicles. Specimen CCZ _ 103 C in situ image H dorsal ossicles. Specimen CCZ _ 104 D in situ image E dorsal view of specimen before preservation G ventral view. Scale bars: 5 cm (A, D); 2 cm (B); 1 cm (E, G); 75 μm (F); 100 μm (H). Image attribution: Durden and Smith (A-D); Wiklund, Durden, Drennan, and McQuaid (E, G); Bribiesca-Contreras (F, H)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.82172.figure48" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716374" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">48F, H</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
